  "texts": [
    "Open-Domain Dialogue (ODD) Models finetuned for ODD tend to generate considerably less contextualized responses than models adapted using in-context learning.",
    "In particular, fine-tuning Llama2 C reduces contextualization by 40%, while for Mistral I by 35%.",
    "Similarly, fine-tuning reduces their appropriateness by 30% compared to their in-context learning version.",
    "This contrasts with automatic evaluation (Table 2), where in-context learning obtained a higher perplexity (i.e.",
    "worse results) compared to fine-tuning."
  ],
